trans-unit.source: Get User's Group Memberships (intransitive)
trans-unit.target: Get User's Group Memberships (intransitive)

trans-unit.source: The User <embeddedLabel>memberOf</embeddedLabel> operation gets the groups that a specified user is a member of.
trans-unit.target: The User <embeddedLabel>memberOf</embeddedLabel> operation gets the groups that a specified user is a member of.

trans-unit.source: The operation is intransitive, that is, it will only return groups that the object is a direct member of.
trans-unit.target: The operation is intransitive, that is, it will only return groups that the object is a direct member of.

trans-unit.source: This is unlike the <embeddedLabel>isMemberOf</embeddedLabel> function of the directory service, which is transitive and which will return <languageKeyword>true</languageKeyword> if the object being tested is a member of a group either directly or through the object’s membership in another group.
trans-unit.target: This is unlike the <embeddedLabel>isMemberOf</embeddedLabel> function of the directory service, which is transitive and which will return <languageKeyword>true</languageKeyword> if the object being tested is a member of a group either directly or through the object’s membership in another group.

trans-unit.source: The <embeddedLabel>memberOf</embeddedLabel> operation can also be performed on groups and contacts.
trans-unit.target: The <embeddedLabel>memberOf</embeddedLabel> operation can also be performed on groups and contacts.

trans-unit.target: The request may be constructed as follows.

trans-unit.source: Replace <parameterReference>mytenantdomain</parameterReference> with the domain of your Azure Active Directory tenant, such as <parameterReference>contoso.onmicrosoft.com</parameterReference>.
trans-unit.target: Replace <parameterReference>mytenantdomain</parameterReference> with the domain of your Azure Active Directory tenant, such as <parameterReference>contoso.onmicrosoft.com</parameterReference>.

trans-unit.source: The <parameterReference>api-version</parameterReference> query string parameter is required.
trans-unit.target: The <parameterReference>api-version</parameterReference> query string parameter is required.

trans-unit.source: If “$links” is included in the URI, then the response will contain only links to the relevant directory objects.
trans-unit.target: If “$links” is included in the URI, then the response will contain only links to the relevant directory objects.

trans-unit.source: If “$links” is omitted from the URI, the objects themselves are returned.
trans-unit.target: If “$links” is omitted from the URI, the objects themselves are returned.

trans-unit.source: Either <embeddedLabel>objectId</embeddedLabel> or <embeddedLabel>userPrincipalName</embeddedLabel> may be used to specify the target user.
trans-unit.target: Either <embeddedLabel>objectId</embeddedLabel> or <embeddedLabel>userPrincipalName</embeddedLabel> may be used to specify the target user.

trans-unit.source: To return group memberships for a group, specify “groups” as the resource set; for a contact, specify “contacts”.
trans-unit.target: To return group memberships for a group, specify “groups” as the resource set; for a contact, specify “contacts”.

trans-unit.source: You can also specify “directoryObjects” as the resource set; for example, https://graph.windows.net/contoso.onmicrosoft.com/directoryObjects/5e624f44-d38d-4943-b07c-2bad078f52ff/members?api-version=2013-04-05.
trans-unit.target: You can also specify “directoryObjects” as the resource set; for example, https://graph.windows.net/contoso.onmicrosoft.com/directoryObjects/5e624f44-d38d-4943-b07c-2bad078f52ff/members?api-version=2013-04-05.
